was the chief legal – he headed up the Legal

00:44:19.930 --> 00:44:25.150
Department at Microsoft for a long time. About
20 years. He took on the Federal Government

00:44:25.150 --> 00:44:31.120
and anti-trust legislation. I don't think
he's afraid of anybody and he's gonna continue

00:44:31.120 --> 00:44:36.671
to defend the territorial rights as far as
he can go. The reason it's so important to

00:44:36.671 --> 00:44:41.890
the Giants is because, if you look at their
stadium signage, if you look at their season

00:44:41.890 --> 00:44:48.410
ticket base, if you look at all of their minority
owners, there's –Silicon Valley is incredibly

00:44:48.410 --> 00:44:54.940
well represented and they realize the financial
and corporate strength here in Silicon Valley.

00:44:54.940 --> 00:44:59.960
It almost doesn't matter what your market
size is anymore. It matters what you can draw

00:44:59.960 --> 00:45:03.640
from what your corporate base is like. And
that's why you've got a team like the Arizona

00:45:03.640 --> 00:45:10.020
Diamondbacks in Phoenix being a huge metro
area. But the average income in Phoenix is

00:45:10.020 --> 00:45:13.231
the lowest of any major league city and that's
why their ticket prices are so low and they

00:45:13.231 --> 00:45:17.430
still can't get anybody to come to the ballpark.
So I think the Giants realize that the South

00:45:17.430 --> 00:45:24.890
Bay is a big part of their revenue stream,
a big part of their, their base of season

00:45:24.890 --> 00:45:28.790
ticket holders and sponsors. And they don't
wanna let go of that. They don't want the

00:45:28.790 --> 00:45:33.510
A's to move there. And if the A's – basically
it's a siege mentality. They're trying to

00:45:33.510 --> 00:45:37.890
starve them out. And if the A's don't wanna
build in, in Oakland, I would love to see

00:45:37.890 --> 00:45:41.430
them build a park in Jacklin Square. It would
be great. I lived in Oakland for a few years

00:45:41.430 --> 00:45:45.810
and I happen to like Oakland and I'd like
to see the A's stay there. But if that can't

00:45:45.810 --> 00:45:50.420
happen, the Giants are going to do everything
they can to try to keep the A's out of San

00:45:50.420 --> 00:45:56.270
Jose. And this blue ribbon committee, I have
the very fun job of trying to talk to Bud

00:45:56.270 --> 00:45:59.890
Selig every All Star Game when he does his
luncheon with the baseball writers and ask

00:45:59.890 --> 00:46:04.360
him about the A's and the San Jose question.
And I get to see him do his soft shoe tap

00:46:04.360 --> 00:46:08.620
dance, every single time. [laughter] And,
and he basically says, 'Well the committee's

00:46:08.620 --> 00:46:15.190
still meeting. So.' [laughter] The committee
has been meeting for a long, long time. So

00:46:15.190 --> 00:46:20.190
basically though if Bud says that it's something
that they are going to let the A's pursue,

00:46:20.190 --> 00:46:24.150
it takes a three-quarters vote of the owners
to overturn the territorial rights. Plus it

00:46:24.150 --> 00:46:29.700
means so much money for the owners. So I really
do believe that if he says, 'This is the position

00:46:29.700 --> 00:46:35.390
that I'm advocating', the owners will follow
suit. So basically they just need to convince

00:46:35.390 --> 00:46:41.381
Bud Selig that that it would be bad for both
teams in the Bay Area to have the A's in the

00:46:41.381 --> 00:46:45.780
South Bay. And the jury's still out.
