00:48:07.850 --> 00:48:14.780
So I think they realize that to a degree it's
a little unsustainable to go 14 and 3 in one

00:48:14.780 --> 00:48:20.390
run games and the bullpen can't pitch as well
as it's pitched all year. The starters are

00:48:20.390 --> 00:48:23.900
gonna have days where their arms are dragging.
And they're gonna have to score more runs

00:48:23.900 --> 00:48:28.600
and I think that they realize this. Whether
it means that they just, they'll bring up

00:48:28.600 --> 00:48:32.640
Brendan Belt at some point to help the offense
or they'll make another trade or adjustment.

00:48:32.640 --> 00:48:36.210
You have to constantly be looking for ways
to get better. And that's certainly what they

00:48:36.210 --> 00:48:41.480
did last year in overhauling the roster during
the year. So they do realize that they've

00:48:41.480 --> 00:48:44.590
gotta go out there and produce and if they
don't, then somebody else is probably going

00:48:44.590 --> 00:48:51.790
to get their at-bats. So they're still finding
their identity as an offensive team but certainly

00:48:51.790 --> 00:48:56.730
they're pitching as well as they ever have.
And I think we just all saw that pitching

00:48:56.730 --> 00:49:00.980
wins championships. So you have to like their
position right now because they're in first

00:49:00.980 --> 00:49:05.421
place by what -- three and a half, four games
and you know that there's a lot they're not

00:49:05.421 --> 00:49:11.750
doing right. So who knows? Maybe we'll have
a sequel. [audience chuckles]

00:49:11.750 --> 00:49:16.590
So thank you everyone for coming out. I really
appreciate it.

00:49:16.590 --> 00:49:17.140
[applause]

